# Ros2 and Autoware commands and tricks

## How to know which file from src/universe/autoware_universe/control/autoware_vehicle_cmd_gate/config/vehicle_cmd_gate.param.yaml or src/launcher/autoware_launch/autoware_launch/config/control/vehicle_cmd_gate/vehicle_cmd_gate.param.yaml is used effectively, in order to patch the right file and not the wrong file?

VSCode Continue "Quen3-code-next" answers: 

You need to know which launch file is being used — the one from autoware_launch or autoware_universe.

✅ Check which launch is active:
Run
ros2 launch autoware_launch e2e_simulator.launch.xml --show-args
# Look for vehicle_cmd_gate param path
Or, more directly:

Run
ros2 param dump /control/vehicle_cmd_gate | grep -E "stop_hold_acceleration|emergency_acceleration"
# This shows the *runtime values* used
✅ Check which node is using which config
Run
ros2 node info /control/vehicle_cmd_gate
# Look for parameter sources
Then:

Run
ros2 param get /control/vehicle_cmd_gate stop_hold_acceleration
# Shows value used at runtime
🔍 Most reliable: trace launch hierarchy
Find which launch file loads vehicle_cmd_gate:

Run
grep -r "vehicle_cmd_gate" ./src/launcher/autoware_launch/autoware_launch/ | grep -E "\.launch|\.xml"
# Likely:
# ./src/launcher/autoware_launch/autoware_launch/config/control/vehicle_cmd_gate/vehicle_cmd_gate.param.yaml
Also:

Run
grep -r "vehicle_cmd_gate" ./src/universe/autoware_universe/control/autoware_vehicle_cmd_gate/launch/ | grep -E "\.launch|\.xml"
# Likely:
# ./src/universe/autoware_universe/control/autoware_vehicle_cmd_gate/launch/vehicle_cmd_gate.launch.xml
→ Whichever one is included in your main launch file is the one used.

From your earlier:

Run
ros2 launch autoware_launch e2e_simulator.launch.xml ...
→ So the autoware_launch config is used, not autoware_universe.

✅ Final answer
Since you're launching with:

Run
ros2 launch autoware_launch e2e_simulator.launch.xml ...
→ The effective config is:

Run
./src/launcher/autoware_launch/autoware_launch/config/control/vehicle_cmd_gate/vehicle_cmd_gate.param.yaml
→ Patch that file, not the autoware_universe one.

